{"TopicId":177229,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Mars \u0026#039;impossible\u0026quot; to terraform","CreatedByName":"TheGuyNamedAlan","CreatedById":162058,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-01T23:41:54Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T14:17:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533909774\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf martian gravity is weaker than earth, it is bad for human health. But does that also makes crops grow bigger? Since they had to fight less against gravity to grow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlants grow toward the light, not away from the ground, so gravity won\u0027t make much of a difference there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanted in lower gravity, crops which grow larger and produce more will quickly be selected for, so even if it is not an immediate outcome it will be the eventual outcome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T14:21:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431299\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533910663\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwill quickly be selected for\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the Earth their productivty is limited not just by gravity, btw. If they can make it twice, they can do this on Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a twice bigger tomato with twice thicker fibers would not be a fine result.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T14:22:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533908874\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ejust a few places you can grow multiple crops a year.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt means a higher crop production in one area. Which means you need less land to get the same amount of harvest. Which means less resources used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCombine that with slightly less consumption per capita plus other sources of food\u00A0and you get the reason why \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EJava\u003C/a\u003E can sustain a population density of 1000/sq km (3000/sq mi) easily. (this is on par with \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EBangladesh\u003C/a\u003E.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0We also rely on rice, which hasn\u0027t changed too much from their wild counterparts AFAIK.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431291\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533909774\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E does that also makes crops grow bigger? Since they had to fight less against gravity to grow?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really, it could be larger but emptier (idk but here we would call it\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ekopong\u003C/em\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-10T14:50:15Z\u0022 title=\u002208/10/2018 02:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T14:51:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533910910\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the Earth their productivty is limited not just by gravity, btw. If they can make it twice, they can do this on Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, a twice bigger tomato with twice thicker fibers would not be a fine result.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have long selected grain with short stalks, we don\u0027t want the plant to use a lot of energy growing an long stalk then all the plants in the field are the same.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAncient\u00A0wheat was almost man high.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T15:10:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533912676\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E have long selected grain with short stalks, we don\u0027t want the plant to use a lot of \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eenergy growing an long stalk then all the plants in the field are the same\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E.\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... unless you\u0027re \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deepwater_rice\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egrowing them in floodplains\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T15:11:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn emblem of future Martian terraformers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022200px-Camp-Fire-Badge.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022199\u0022 src=\u0022http://wiki.scouts.ca/English/images/thumb/8/8c/Camp-Fire-Badge.png/200px-Camp-Fire-Badge.png\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt represents their motto.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022A lot of wood and air with oxygen!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTheir insignia.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCrossed tools.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wooden-block-plane_cut_cmyk.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022427\u0022 src=\u0022https://keyassets.timeincuk.net/inspirewp/live/wp-content/uploads/sites/19/2015/06/wooden-block-plane_cut_cmyk.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002268251173-two-man-saw-icon-in-black-style\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://previews.123rf.com/images/pandavector/pandavector1611/pandavector161100301/68251173-two-man-saw-icon-in-black-style-isolated-on-white-background-sawmill-and-timber-symbol-vector-illust.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022768\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSawing a corn stem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hqdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022360\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/x3-s6j3lDq4/hqdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-10T15:13:28Z\u0022 title=\u002208/10/2018 03:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JERONIMO","CreatedById":188491,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T15:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoesn\u0027t make sence to teraform it... let\u0027s just close our eyes on mars and give a minute of silence to venus. rip venus. no body lovd planet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T17:09:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533915502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188491\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JERONIMO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JERONIMO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoesn\u0027t make sence to teraform it... let\u0027s just close our eyes on mars and give a minute of silence to venus. rip venus. no body lovd planet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Venus, just bioengineer some sort of algal colony that takes in sunlight, metabolizes CO2 and produces O2 in a bladder that slowly inflates/grows, and reproduces by budding. Seed the Venusian atmosphere with the stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T03:32:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431388\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533920954\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Venus, just bioengineer some sort of algal colony that takes in sunlight, metabolizes CO2 and produces O2 in a bladder that slowly inflates/grows, and reproduces by budding. Seed the Venusian atmosphere with the stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow thick are algae clouds in the Earth atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T20:43:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533958367\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow thick are algae clouds in the Earth atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout as thick as the buoyancy of O\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E in dry air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVenus\u0027s dry air is a helluvalot denser than our dry air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T21:16:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432138\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534020200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout as thick as the buoyancy of O\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E in dry air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVenus\u0027s dry air is a helluvalot denser than our dry air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlgae are still much denser.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd they have to float above clouds, where \u0022air\u0022 density is much less than on surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T01:37:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think Mars\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ecan\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ebe made to support plants, an ocean, and humans without spacesuits. However, I think it would require some effort to keep it that way for millions of years, i.e. a giant magnet at Mars-Sun L1, constant atmosphere replenishing, or a combination of the two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T14:04:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534022167\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlgae are still much denser.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd they have to float above clouds, where \u0022air\u0022 density is much less than on surface.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t matter, because it\u0027s an issue of composition. Pure\u00A0oxygen (or even ordinary dry Earth air) is less dense than Venus\u0027s carbon-dioxide atmosphere at\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eany\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ealtitude, and so it will be more buoyant regardless of where it floats.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest challenge would be bioengineering an algae capable of metabolizing hydrogen disulfide in place of water; there are trace amounts of water vapor in the Venusian atmosphere, but it\u0027s not enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-12T14:05:01Z\u0022 title=\u002208/12/2018 02:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 12, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by sevenperforce\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T14:25:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534082681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t matter, because it\u0027s an issue of composition.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSize matters. Smaller and lighter particles float better than big and heavy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf spread in air a cloud of bacteria here on Earth, how long will it exist?\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven lightweight virus particles do not float in air, and neither green clouds I can remember outdoors. \u003Csub\u003E(Except of \u003Cem\u003EPathologic\u003C/em\u003E game, of course)\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T14:53:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534083958\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSize matters. Smaller and lighter particles float better than big and heavy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich is why both diatomic nitrogen and diatomic oxygen float in an atmosphere of carbon dioxide and sulfuric acid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEach carbon dioxide molecule masses 44 amu. Diatomic nitrogen molecules mass 28 amu. Diatomic oxygen molecules mass 32 amu.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo matter where you are in the Venusian atmosphere, a balloon or bladder filled with oxygen will float, because oxygen is lighter than carbon dioxide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf spread in air a cloud of bacteria here on Earth, how long will it exist?\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven lightweight virus particles do not float in air, and neither green clouds I can remember outdoors. \u003Csub\u003E(Except of \u003Cem\u003EPathologic\u003C/em\u003E game, of course)\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.hardydiagnostics.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Ice-Forming-Bacteria.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMicrobial colonies grow and thrive in Earth\u0027s clouds.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T15:45:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, earth\u0027s lower atmosphere is full of microbial life, that is known since the early 19th century. There has been recent work on this as well, including the stratosphere. There is little because big fat inversion below (tropopause, very little exchange), but still some, spit up by volcanoes or maybe lifted by extraordinary well developed frontal systems or storms.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-12T15:47:41Z\u0022 title=\u002208/12/2018 03:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 12, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T16:26:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the atmosphere is full of life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd how much life is there\u00A0in atmosphere compared\u00A0to the land life?\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhere are photosynthesizing green clouds?\u003Cbr\u003E\nFor sure, the evolution should make them if could.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-12T16:28:31Z\u0022 title=\u002208/12/2018 04:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 12, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T19:00:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432622\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534091207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere are photosynthesizing green clouds?\u003Cbr\u003E\nFor sure, the evolution should make them if could.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot enough time for evolution to work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T22:00:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow to terraform Mars based from lowest to highest tech level:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Spam nuclear bombs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Build atmosphere generator facility\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Bioengineer plant or algae to live on Mars and generate atmosphere\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Tele-portals\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MDZhB","CreatedById":99243,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T22:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I know this discussion is about terraforming Mars and all, but what\u0027s the deal with wanting to live on that rock anyway? Like Green Baron said on page 1, the soil is poisonous, there\u0027s nothing to eat, drink, or breathe, and on top of those things, there is none of the ozone that protects us here on Earth. All things the same, wouldn\u0027t it be safer to build space stations in orbit? That would mean no fuel needed for landing/takeoff, no landing legs, no parachutes, no sanitation rooms, etc. And, we could make our own gravity \u003Cem\u003Ea la\u003C/em\u003E 2001. Not to mention that there would basically be no size restraint. I think the only hazard that we would be more likely to encounter in orbit as opposed to the surface would be micrometeorites, but we already have experience with that. Given enough time, we could even add radiation shielding (or even create some from dirt brought up from below)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-13T22:06:50Z\u0022 title=\u002208/13/2018 10:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 13, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by MDZhB\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T22:31:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534197807\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299243\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MDZhB\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, MDZhB said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I know this discussion is about terraforming Mars and all, but what\u0027s the deal with wanting to live on that rock anyway? Like Green Baron said on page 1, the soil is poisonous, there\u0027s nothing to eat, drink, or breathe, and on top of those things, there is none of the ozone that protects us here on Earth. All things the same, wouldn\u0027t it be safer to build space stations in orbit? That would mean no fuel needed for landing/takeoff, no landing legs, no parachutes, no sanitation rooms, etc. And, we could make our own gravity \u003Cem\u003Ea la\u003C/em\u003E 2001. Not to mention that there would basically be no size restraint. I think the only hazard that we would be more likely to encounter in orbit as opposed to the surface would be micrometeorites, but we already have experience with that. Given enough time, we could even add radiation shielding (or even create some from dirt brought up from below)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, Mars has water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T22:42:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534199464\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, Mars has water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo does Antarctica, but you don\u0027t see people clamoring to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T23:00:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433399\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534200145\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo does Antarctica, but you don\u0027t see people clamoring to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure a great many fine scientists would take exception to\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T23:26:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433410\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534201201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure a great many fine scientists would take exception to\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, fine. A couple thousand people out of 7 billion want to go somewhere that is infinitely more reachable and life-friendly than Mars. You got me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MDZhB","CreatedById":99243,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-14T00:56:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534199464\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, Mars has water.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight, but there\u0027s no need to actually live there to get it. If I had the resources to create a Mars colony, I would put most of the infrastructure and people in low orbit, and have ferries to go up and down to get whatever is needed from the surface, such as water, soil, ores, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}